Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
loadIoFile(25.10)                                            loadIoFile(25.10)

Name
       loadIoFile - Loads an I/O assignment file

Syntax
        loadIoFile

       [-help]

       <file_name>

       [-noAdjustDieSize]

       [-specifiedIosOnly]

       [-ECO [-padsOnly | -bumpsOnly]]

       Loads  an I/O assignment file. You can use this command after importing
       the design.

       Notes:

              * By default, the loadIoFile command will  automatically  adjust
                the  die  size  to accommodate all the IOs. If this command is
                used after floorplanning, it would change the die size defined
                in the floorplan file. If you do not want the die size  to  be
                automatically adjusted, use the -noAdjustDieSize parameter.

              * During I/O inst placement, the space value determines the dis-
                tance between the current inst and the previous inst. Earlier,
                while  honoring  iopad spacing, the loadIoFile command consid-
                ers the previous inst to be the inst that appears  before  the
                current  inst  when  insts  are  placed according the io_order
                specified in the I/O assignment file .

Parameters
       -bumpsOnly
              Loads only bump ECO operations in specified IO file.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -ECO   Allows I/O ECO change by loading a new I/O file. In a chip-pack-
              age co-design situation, when I/O Planner (IOP) utility  in  SiP
              is used for modifying the I/O and bump information, the modified
              information  needs  to be passed to Innovus. When -ECO is speci-
              fied, loadIoFile overwrites the existing setting  for  I/Os  and
              bumps with the information from the new I/O file.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       <file_name>
              Specifies the name of the I/O assignment file.

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each loadIoFile  parameter.For  a  detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command:

              man loadIoFile

       -noAdjustDieSize
              Specifies that the die size should  not  be  adjusted  automati-
              cally.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -padsOnly
              Loads only IO pad ECO operations in the specified IO file.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -specifiedIosOnly
              Loads  only  the IO in the specified IO file. This parameter en-
              ables you to place IO cells listed in the  I/O  assignment  file
              without  deleting  or  moving the IO cells not listed in I/O as-
              signment file.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
       The following command loads the I/O assignment file myPinFile.io:

       loadIoFile myPinFile.io

